snippet.textDisplay:
Many people making comments do not seem to understand that having a visa is not a guarantee to entry into any country. The final decision in every single country is made by the immigration officials at the point of entry. If they discover an error they can and often do refuse entry. 

From the evidence so far it seems that Tennis Australia gave players incorrect information regarding exemptions.

Once the immigration officials found Djokovic did not meet the entry requirements they probably had little choice but to cancel his visa.

Having worked in this field, I expect Djokovic will be deported in the next couple of days.
